The first assignment consists of a curriculum graph programmed in Prolog, that
features some useful functions to check some aspects of the graph, such as
pre-requisites or which semester a class belongs to.

Original assignment: a68d5f3202e53151b2f0c98f278e689645e125c6

The second assignment deals with creating polygons and outputting them to
SVG pictures, by making a turtle from the Logo programming language produce
line graphics.

Original assignment: 8f862129b839193fe2ce8957cdb6e04c778792d0

The third assignment builds on some tools to classify PGM image files
according to image moments.

Original assignment: 10b04e3b15b52deecaa2080d44c7b28dc38efedc
